1
00:00:40,291 --> 00:00:41,625
Thank you.

2
00:00:49,675 --> 00:00:50,801
Hello.

3
00:00:55,389 --> 00:01:07,359
A MAN

4
00:01:09,153 --> 00:01:14,492
<i>"Seibundo Stationery Store"</i>

5
00:02:22,309 --> 00:02:23,644
Hello.

6
00:03:03,309 --> 00:03:04,768
Thank you.

7
00:03:09,481 --> 00:03:11,358
2,030 yen.

8
00:03:16,488 --> 00:03:18,365
2,030 yen exactly.

9
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,510
Where's the breaker?

10
00:03:40,554 --> 00:03:42,306
Those lights are on.

11
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,115
Sorry.

12
00:04:03,118 --> 00:04:05,829
It's... Sorry, it's there.

13
00:04:15,798 --> 00:04:17,549
Thank you.

14
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:23,472
Thank you.

15
00:04:52,793 --> 00:04:53,877
'Morning.

16
00:04:54,003 --> 00:04:55,087
'Morning.

17
00:04:58,716 --> 00:05:03,721
Yuto, could you take that
lotus root in for me?

18
00:05:12,855 --> 00:05:14,648
Mom, breakfast.

19
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:22,573
We're gonna eat.

20
00:05:28,871 --> 00:05:30,873
This lotus root's good.

21
00:05:31,206 --> 00:05:32,666
Want pickles?

22
00:05:43,052 --> 00:05:44,720
Wait up!

23
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:46,889
Too slow, Yuto!

24
00:05:57,941 --> 00:05:59,234
Yuto!

25
00:06:19,922 --> 00:06:21,924
I've been thinking lately.

26
00:06:22,091 --> 00:06:25,552
My husband went to Heaven before me,

27
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:30,265
so little Ryo won't get lonely there.

28
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:37,106
Masahiro was so selfless.
He always put his grandchild first.

29
00:06:44,822 --> 00:06:46,198
I'm home!

30
00:06:46,824 --> 00:06:47,991
Hey there Yuto.

31
00:06:48,075 --> 00:06:49,493
Yuto, hey there.

32
00:06:49,576 --> 00:06:53,705
Mrs. Okumura brought us
cakes from Taiseido.

33
00:06:53,789 --> 00:06:55,582
Strawberry, and Mont Blanc.

34
00:06:55,707 --> 00:06:57,042
No way!

35
00:06:58,961 --> 00:07:00,546
In the fridge.

36
00:07:05,676 --> 00:07:06,885
Mom.

37
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:11,598
You've got Yuto.
Better toughen up, Hatsue.

38
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:15,644
It's hardest on Rie, you know.

39
00:07:15,936 --> 00:07:18,939
She came back from Yokohama single.

40
00:07:20,983 --> 00:07:22,693
Thank you.

41
00:07:24,570 --> 00:07:27,030
This is 1,785 yen, and...

42
00:07:27,739 --> 00:07:30,200
Mister, you paint for a hobby?

43
00:07:31,994 --> 00:07:38,208
One of my customers saw you,
on the grass near Kiyose River.

44
00:07:39,251 --> 00:07:41,253
Show me sometime!

45
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:43,213
It's not worth it.

46
00:07:43,297 --> 00:07:45,716
Rie, don't you wanna see?

47
00:07:47,676 --> 00:07:50,721
Mrs. Okumura,
mind your business.

48
00:07:53,765 --> 00:07:56,768
Hatsue, the other day...

49
00:08:01,273 --> 00:08:02,357
Daisuke.

50
00:08:04,067 --> 00:08:07,196
Its balance tells you
where to land it.

51
00:08:08,238 --> 00:08:13,076
This tree'll fall easiest there.
Got it?

52
00:08:14,203 --> 00:08:15,746
See its balance?

53
00:08:16,914 --> 00:08:18,290
It's on a lean.

54
00:08:20,042 --> 00:08:24,087
So, cut a notch facing
where you want it to fall.

55
00:08:24,254 --> 00:08:27,257
Kuroki! Quit waffling already!

56
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:29,218
Shut your trap!

57
00:08:29,301 --> 00:08:31,929
Telling him ain't gonna help.

58
00:08:32,221 --> 00:08:33,305
Watch me.

59
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:20,477
Daisuke.

60
00:09:21,436 --> 00:09:22,479
Try it.

61
00:09:24,398 --> 00:09:28,151
<i>Where's that Daisuke Taniguchi from?</i>

62
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:35,450
Ikaho Onsen in Gunma. He's the
second son of an innkeeper there.

63
00:09:36,827 --> 00:09:38,954
A grand old inn.

64
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:43,208
So why's a guy like him
out here working the forests?

65
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,919
Doesn't it sound fishy to you?

66
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:50,424
I'll admit,
it doesn't sound normal.

67
00:09:51,008 --> 00:09:55,846
But nobody lives their life
without picking up a few scars.

68
00:09:56,305 --> 00:09:57,931
Is he an ex-con?

69
00:09:58,515 --> 00:10:03,437
Can't have him starting trouble.
Seems kinda like a downer.

70
00:10:03,979 --> 00:10:07,399
He's not a downer.
He's just quiet.

71
00:10:08,025 --> 00:10:10,027
A fast learner too.

72
00:10:10,861 --> 00:10:14,031
Much more useful than your brother.

73
00:10:14,281 --> 00:10:16,533
Leave Takeshi out of it.

74
00:10:17,034 --> 00:10:20,037
Anyway, he's a good kid.

75
00:10:20,287 --> 00:10:22,414
I like Daisuke.

76
00:10:50,984 --> 00:10:52,152
Hello.

77
00:11:10,962 --> 00:11:14,132
Thank you.
That'll be 200 yen.

78
00:11:16,093 --> 00:11:17,427
Do you need a bag?

79
00:11:17,511 --> 00:11:18,887
I'm fine.

80
00:11:21,932 --> 00:11:24,101
1,000 yen received.

81
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,480
Need a receipt?

82
00:11:28,605 --> 00:11:29,940
I don't.

83
00:11:33,110 --> 00:11:35,320
Here, 800 yen change.

84
00:11:35,987 --> 00:11:37,114
Um...

85
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:42,953
These are...my paintings.

86
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:47,124
You brought them for me?

87
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:49,918
They're not great though.

88
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:52,629
May I?

89
00:12:16,194 --> 00:12:18,238
You obviously love painting.

90
00:12:20,490 --> 00:12:21,992
This is great.

91
00:12:27,706 --> 00:12:30,500
This kinda looks like Yuto.

92
00:12:32,711 --> 00:12:35,046
My son plays there a lot.

93
00:12:39,509 --> 00:12:43,263
Is he the boy I saw here before?

94
00:12:43,555 --> 00:12:46,641
I-I think that might actually be him.

95
00:12:46,725 --> 00:12:50,187
Oh, really?
I guess it must be.

96
00:12:51,021 --> 00:12:53,023
That's kinda cool.

97
00:12:56,193 --> 00:12:57,360
Really great...

98
00:12:57,444 --> 00:13:00,405
If it's okay,
could we be friends?

99
00:13:06,703 --> 00:13:09,998
Of course not.
You're married. I'm sorry.

100
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:14,711
Well, I'm not married.
I...

101
00:13:15,545 --> 00:13:18,215
...have a son,
but I'm divorced.

102
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:22,219
Oh, is that right...

103
00:13:22,344 --> 00:13:24,721
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

104
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,602
If you knew,
that'd be freaky.

105
00:13:31,603 --> 00:13:35,607
Oh yes. You're right.
That would be.

106
00:13:36,566 --> 00:13:38,276
Thank you.

107
00:13:38,777 --> 00:13:41,321
Er, what's your name?

108
00:13:44,115 --> 00:13:45,534
Taniguchi.

109
00:13:52,332 --> 00:13:55,835
Sorry it's crumpled.
I'm Daisuke Taniguchi.

110
00:14:04,761 --> 00:14:08,765
Sorry, I don't have a card.
I'm Rie Takemoto.

111
00:14:09,808 --> 00:14:11,101
Rie.

112
00:14:13,270 --> 00:14:17,357
Come anytime,
and show me your paintings.

113
00:14:23,154 --> 00:14:25,156
No need to buy anything.

114
00:14:41,548 --> 00:14:42,716
Done it before?

115
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:45,218
Yuto had a younger brother.

116
00:14:50,473 --> 00:14:52,809
But he died when he was 2.

117
00:14:57,647 --> 00:14:59,649
Mind if I tell you?

118
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:08,825
A brain disease.

119
00:15:10,493 --> 00:15:12,746
I thought he'd get over it...

120
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:20,503
...but it turned out to be malignant.

121
00:15:31,348 --> 00:15:35,685
Was that...the reason?

122
00:15:39,522 --> 00:15:42,317
You broke up with your husband.

123
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:56,456
We disagreed over treatment.

124
00:15:58,249 --> 00:16:04,381
From then on,
nothing went our way.

125
00:16:14,683 --> 00:16:17,560
If I'd known nothing would work...

126
00:16:18,728 --> 00:16:22,232
I would've let him eat what he wanted,

127
00:16:23,775 --> 00:16:29,239
taken him to his favorite zoo,
as much as he wanted...

128
00:16:35,412 --> 00:16:37,414
At the very least...

129
00:16:39,624 --> 00:16:41,418
At the very least...

130
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:45,922
...I wanted him to
feel glad that he lived.

131
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:04,357
The radiation treatment
was so hard on him...

132
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:09,946
I'd put him through so much pain...

133
00:17:20,582 --> 00:17:22,250
But...

134
00:17:25,503 --> 00:17:28,548
When I realized it was for nothing...

135
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,470
I felt so...

136
00:17:48,234 --> 00:17:51,946
Your son...
What was his name?

137
00:18:01,873 --> 00:18:03,291
Ryo.

138
00:18:05,585 --> 00:18:06,586
Ryo.

139
00:18:09,464 --> 00:18:10,924
Little Ryo.

140
00:18:19,724 --> 00:18:21,059
Little Ryo.

141
00:18:27,732 --> 00:18:28,942
Here goes.

142
00:18:38,535 --> 00:18:39,744
You're good.

143
00:18:41,538 --> 00:18:43,873
Over here. Go!

144
00:18:46,042 --> 00:18:47,544
Pass to your mom.

145
00:18:49,337 --> 00:18:50,588
To me?

146
00:19:01,516 --> 00:19:04,561
Run!
Run, run! Run!

147
00:19:07,730 --> 00:19:10,024
Hurry! Hurry!

148
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:45,912
It's okay, it's okay.
It's okay, it's okay!

149
00:20:46,454 --> 00:20:47,664
There there.

150
00:20:49,123 --> 00:20:52,710
It's okay, it's okay.
It's okay, it's okay.

151
00:21:19,696 --> 00:21:20,905
Finished?

152
00:21:22,699 --> 00:21:24,242
Looks cute!

153
00:21:25,827 --> 00:21:29,205
Did we forget anything?
All okay?

154
00:21:30,748 --> 00:21:32,041
Can you do it?

155
00:21:42,135 --> 00:21:44,679
Look, you got food on you.

156
00:21:44,762 --> 00:21:45,888
Yum.

157
00:21:51,227 --> 00:21:52,895
Eat nicely!

158
00:21:59,027 --> 00:22:02,030
Hey, don't play with food!

159
00:22:09,912 --> 00:22:11,789
You're late for school!

160
00:22:12,790 --> 00:22:15,293
He is.
Go on, get moving.

161
00:22:18,004 --> 00:22:20,590
You didn't eat this?
Want more?

162
00:22:20,715 --> 00:22:21,924
Hey, Dad.

163
00:22:22,884 --> 00:22:24,093
Can I go?

164
00:22:24,218 --> 00:22:26,596
Huh? What?

165
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:28,931
What? Say that again.

166
00:22:29,557 --> 00:22:30,558
To the mountains.

167
00:22:30,641 --> 00:22:31,809
Huh? What?

168
00:22:31,934 --> 00:22:32,894
The mountains...

169
00:22:33,186 --> 00:22:34,270
Like hell you can.

170
00:22:34,896 --> 00:22:36,022
Sports day training.

171
00:22:36,105 --> 00:22:37,607
So what?

172
00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:39,275
It's no big deal.

173
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:41,944
- Hana, say "No way."
- No way!

174
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:43,780
See? Hana said so.

175
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:45,656
Hana, say it again.

176
00:22:46,324 --> 00:22:48,701
What did you say?
"No way."

177
00:22:48,785 --> 00:22:49,952
No way!

178
00:22:50,078 --> 00:22:51,204
You're so late.

179
00:22:53,122 --> 00:22:55,750
Come on!
Come on, go already!

180
00:22:58,336 --> 00:22:59,629
Take care!

181
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:05,718
Daisuke.

182
00:23:07,178 --> 00:23:09,639
Oh. Sorry, sorry.

183
00:23:12,975 --> 00:23:13,935
Thanks.

184
00:23:17,313 --> 00:23:18,314
Thanks.

185
00:23:18,439 --> 00:23:19,107
See you.

186
00:23:19,315 --> 00:23:20,108
Bye.

187
00:23:20,191 --> 00:23:21,609
Take care.

188
00:23:42,588 --> 00:23:43,673
Get in.

189
00:23:44,757 --> 00:23:46,175
What about school?

190
00:23:46,509 --> 00:23:47,635
Come on.

191
00:24:03,359 --> 00:24:06,070
Busy day today.
Let's do this.

192
00:24:10,199 --> 00:24:13,411
Dad Dad Dad!
Which one?

193
00:24:14,704 --> 00:24:16,164
- Daisuke!
- This one?

194
00:24:16,247 --> 00:24:21,043
We're going further in.
You can finish up here for us.

195
00:24:24,714 --> 00:24:26,007
Work hard, kid.

196
00:24:27,592 --> 00:24:30,887
Yuto, what do you wanna do today?

197
00:24:31,012 --> 00:24:32,263
Make a slingshot.

198
00:24:32,346 --> 00:24:34,223
That again?

199
00:25:43,417 --> 00:25:44,919
Daisuke?

200
00:25:45,419 --> 00:25:46,754
You okay?

201
00:25:47,755 --> 00:25:48,756
Daisuke?

202
00:25:50,132 --> 00:25:53,052
Hey... Hey...
Daisuke?

203
00:25:53,803 --> 00:25:55,137
Hey Daisuke!

204
00:25:55,888 --> 00:25:59,267
Hey! Somebody!
Call the office!

205
00:25:59,976 --> 00:26:04,105
Hey! Daisuke!
Daisuke! Hey!

206
00:26:04,897 --> 00:26:05,898
Ambulance!

207
00:26:05,982 --> 00:26:08,985
Call an ambulance!
Quickly!

208
00:26:09,443 --> 00:26:11,737
Hey! Daisuke!

209
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:58,784
<i>One year later</i>

210
00:26:59,744 --> 00:27:03,748
<i>First anniversary of Daisuke's death</i>

211
00:27:33,778 --> 00:27:35,905
I'll leave you now.

212
00:27:40,284 --> 00:27:43,037
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you so much.

213
00:27:49,919 --> 00:27:51,837
My name's Taniguchi.

214
00:27:54,006 --> 00:27:56,092
Kyoichi Taniguchi.

215
00:27:56,926 --> 00:27:58,844
Thank you for coming so far.

216
00:27:58,969 --> 00:28:02,056
My younger brother caused you trouble.

217
00:28:02,473 --> 00:28:07,186
Not at all. I'm sorry for
not inviting you to the funeral.

218
00:28:08,062 --> 00:28:11,357
I bet he told you not to.
I get it.

219
00:28:11,982 --> 00:28:14,402
Well, actually...

220
00:28:14,527 --> 00:28:20,074
I know we need to discuss
where he'll be interred, so...

221
00:28:20,199 --> 00:28:23,369
Daisuke spoke badly of me,
I presume?

222
00:28:25,538 --> 00:28:31,043
He didn't talk about his past,
but he said he and his family...

223
00:28:31,127 --> 00:28:34,213
No need to say it.
I know.

224
00:28:37,550 --> 00:28:41,887
He caused trouble for so many,
right till the end...

225
00:28:43,973 --> 00:28:47,017
Why was living right so hard for him?

226
00:28:48,352 --> 00:28:53,941
Dying under a tree in this backwater...
An undutiful son to the end.

227
00:28:56,152 --> 00:28:59,113
Oh, incense. May I?

228
00:28:59,405 --> 00:29:01,365
Sure, of course.

229
00:29:03,951 --> 00:29:07,455
Hey, invoice me for
funeral and grave costs.

230
00:29:07,580 --> 00:29:09,165
No, there's no need...

231
00:29:09,248 --> 00:29:11,208
Count on me to pay.

232
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:37,610
You haven't...
put a photo of him here?

233
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:43,282
A photo.
Of the deceased.

234
00:29:43,407 --> 00:29:44,450
Sorry?

235
00:29:46,327 --> 00:29:48,579
I have, right there.

236
00:29:51,457 --> 00:29:52,333
Where?

237
00:29:52,458 --> 00:29:54,126
Er, there.

238
00:29:54,668 --> 00:29:55,669
Where?

239
00:29:59,048 --> 00:30:00,382
Excuse me.

240
00:30:07,306 --> 00:30:09,016
That's not him.

241
00:30:11,310 --> 00:30:14,480
That's not Daisuke.

242
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:16,315
Yes, it is...

243
00:30:16,398 --> 00:30:17,775
No, it's not him.

244
00:30:17,983 --> 00:30:20,653
- It's Daisuke.
- It's not Daisuke.

245
00:30:25,032 --> 00:30:26,575
It's not Daisuke.

246
00:30:27,326 --> 00:30:29,537
Did he change that much?

247
00:30:29,662 --> 00:30:33,999
It's not that.
He's totally different.

248
00:30:34,667 --> 00:30:35,543
I see...

249
00:30:35,668 --> 00:30:37,378
It's a different guy.

250
00:30:41,257 --> 00:30:42,675
It's Daisuke.

251
00:30:44,051 --> 00:30:45,678
It's not Daisuke.

252
00:30:46,053 --> 00:30:51,976
It is. From Ikaho Onsen.
The inn. Tamaki.

253
00:30:54,728 --> 00:30:56,063
It's not Daisuke.

254
00:31:03,070 --> 00:31:06,198
Then, this man...

255
00:31:09,159 --> 00:31:11,078
- Who is he?
- Who is he?

256
00:31:17,626 --> 00:31:20,212
<i>Sorry to interrupt your rest.</i>

257
00:31:21,213 --> 00:31:26,719
<i>We'll be landing at Miyazaki Airport</i>
in approximately 35 minutes.

258
00:31:27,553 --> 00:31:30,514
<i>As the captain mentioned earlier,</i>

259
00:31:31,015 --> 00:31:33,475
<i>in roughly 15 minutes time...</i>

260
00:31:58,667 --> 00:32:01,128
It's been seven years?

261
00:32:01,295 --> 00:32:05,758
Oh, I guess you're right.
Since the divorce proceedings.

262
00:32:07,134 --> 00:32:09,553
Thanks for all you did.

263
00:32:11,055 --> 00:32:13,515
Your son must be big now.

264
00:32:14,516 --> 00:32:16,769
My oldest started junior high.

265
00:32:17,353 --> 00:32:18,395
Your oldest?

266
00:32:19,313 --> 00:32:23,275
Yes, I remarried,
and had a daughter.

267
00:32:24,068 --> 00:32:27,738
Oh, is that so?
How old is she?

268
00:32:28,614 --> 00:32:29,782
She's 4.

269
00:32:30,741 --> 00:32:32,201
Same as mine.

270
00:32:32,534 --> 00:32:34,828
What?
Oh, you too, Mr. Kido?

271
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,122
Me too. I got married.

272
00:32:37,206 --> 00:32:39,416
Oh, is that right...

273
00:32:41,251 --> 00:32:42,753
You've got a daughter?

274
00:32:42,836 --> 00:32:44,129
A son.

275
