pulling off a load of deals.

477
00:51:14,739 --> 00:51:16,532
"Norio Omiura"?

478
00:51:19,327 --> 00:51:22,455
He's in Osaka Prison now.

479
00:51:22,830 --> 00:51:28,419
He was in Osaka when
Daisuke Taniguchi was there too.

480
00:52:01,786 --> 00:52:08,000
Wow, handsome mister lawyer
has come to see little old me.

481
00:52:11,587 --> 00:52:13,339
I'm ugly, ain't I?

482
00:52:14,799 --> 00:52:17,468
No wonder I'm a twisted bastard.

483
00:52:21,848 --> 00:52:25,017
Well, thank you for meeting me.

484
00:52:25,935 --> 00:52:28,437
As I told you, I'm Kido...

485
00:52:28,521 --> 00:52:30,940
You're a Japan-born Korean.

486
00:52:32,859 --> 00:52:33,901
Ain't ya?

487
00:52:39,532 --> 00:52:41,450
Do I have to tell you?

488
00:52:41,534 --> 00:52:44,078
I knew soon as I saw your face.

489
00:52:48,708 --> 00:52:51,627
I'm a naturalized Japanese now.

490
00:52:52,420 --> 00:52:56,674
So, today, as I wrote in my letter,
five years ago...

491
00:52:56,757 --> 00:52:58,384
Mister lawyer.

492
00:52:58,718 --> 00:53:04,891
Some people out there
actually live for 300 years, you know?

493
00:53:07,476 --> 00:53:11,689
I'm sure you've heard
that 300-year-olds are real.

494
00:53:13,941 --> 00:53:15,735
I've never heard that.

495
00:53:16,402 --> 00:53:21,616
Maybe they don't exist in
the world you live in, mister lawyer.

496
00:53:21,741 --> 00:53:27,079
